  "doc_id": "35849",
  "text": "Waterfalls are prominent tourism attractions throughout the world. Waterfalls are generally visited for their aesthetic appeal, for relaxation purposes and in order to take photographs. [CITATION_1] observes that access to waterfall sites is often facilitated by the provision of directional signage, footpaths, lookouts, viewing platforms, handrails, fencing and safety concern information. The more people visit a waterfall, the more likely the site needs these facilities. In recent years, the rise of adventure-related recreational activities has expanded the use of waterfall sites for abseiling, tubing, canyoning and rafting, all of which can change the aesthetic character and relaxation appeal of a waterfall for a significant segment of the visiting public.",
